    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/97.]</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am requested by the Dominican Government to inform you that Haitien forces
                    continue to occupy Dominican territory formerly occupied by Dominican guards,
                    and Haitien authorities are openly aiding the revolutionists of Monte Christi.
                    Demands made by the Dominican Legation for the observance of neutrality have no
                    practical effect. The Monte Cristi revolution would have been suppressed long
                    ago if it had not received Haitien aid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
